With his victory, Alcaraz becomes the highest-paid tennis player, with an estimated $45 million in earnings in 2024.

name: Krejcikova
summary: Barbora Krejcikova emerged victorious in the Wimbledon women's final, defeating Jasmine Paolini in three sets to claim her second Grand Slam singles title. The Czech player, who previously won the French Open in 2021, extended her record over Elena Rybakina to reach her first Wimbledon final. Krejcikova's triumph was the result of a thrilling match with Paolini, and her victory marks a significant milestone in her career. This latest Grand Slam title solidifies Krejcikova's status as one of the top female tennis players in the world.
